HEADWORD: Deportation
<hw>De`por*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>depotatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>d⟦eacute⟧portation</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The act of deporting or exiling, or the state of being deported;
banishment; transportation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In their <qex>deportations</qex>, they had often the favor of
their conquerors.</q> <rj><qau>Atterbury.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>deportee</ent>⟦br⟧
